  "prompt": "What does add on item on Amazon mean?",
  "response": "On Amazon, an \"Add-on Item\" is a product that can only be purchased if your total order meets a minimum spending threshold, typically $25. These are usually lower-priced items that Amazon sells at a very thin margin. Add-on items cannot be shipped separately and must be part of an order that reaches the minimum purchase amount. This allows Amazon to make shipping such small, low-cost items economically feasible. If your order doesn't meet the minimum requirement, you'll need to add more items to your cart to be able to purchase the Add-on Item.",
